Changed functions in video.js
- getVbtAnalysisStatus(data)
  Classifies results as ok, warning, or invalid and returns display/profile eligibility.
- isDisplayableVbtResult(data)
  Reports whether a result can be shown.
- isProfileEligibleVbt(data)
  Reports whether a result can enter personal profile calculations.
- adaptVbtRecord(record)
  Exposes analysis status, displayability, eligibility, and warning details.
- getVelocityProfileComment(records, targetRecord)
  Explains that warning results are saved but excluded from profile calculations.
- renderVbtErrorCard(status)
  Renders a focused error only when no result exists.
- renderVbtResultHero(data, status)
  Renders the main final-rep velocity result and set summary.
- renderRepVelocityCards(metrics)
  Renders mobile-first per-rep cards.
- renderRepVelocityDisplay(data)
  Chooses the rep result presentation.
- renderVbtMeasurementDetails(data)
  Moves measurement conditions into a compact details panel.
- vbtResultMarkup(data)
  Keeps warning results visible instead of replacing them with a retry message.
- saveVbtVelocity(button, mode)
  Persists analysis status and scrolls to the completed result.
- vbtHistoryMarkup(record, records)
  Shows profile adoption or warning status.
- libraryCardMarkup(record)
  Shows saved warning values instead of hiding the measurement.

Behavior contract
- analysisStatus: ok / warning / invalid
- displayableResult: controls whether result metrics are shown
- profileEligible: controls only personal profile aggregation
- Warning results are displayed and saved.
- Invalid/no-result analyses show an error card.

